                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240218-136-off754 t18240218-136-crimeloc757"></join>. On the 19th of January, between five and six o'clock in the evening, a boy ran into the shop, and said I was robbed. I went out - he pointed to the prisoner; I stopped her, and found two shawls on her, which were safe near the door an hour before.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>

               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I saw them laying by the door and picked them up. My husband died this day week.</p>
